  "body": "(Edit by @fvictorio: this issue is blocked by https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/issues/3042)\r\n\r\nWe store our keys (private, Alchemy, Etherscan, etc.) in AWS Secrets Manager. We'd like to pull them directly from there for use in `hardhat.config.ts`. However, this is an asynchronous action and, since Hardhat needs to be loadable via `require` call, configuration must be synchronous.\r\n\r\nHowever, could the library add setters for things like `network` so we can set these values at runtime?\r\n\r\nOur use-case involves running Hardhat in a Fargate container in AWS so setting our private key as an environment variable so it can be read in via `hardhat.config.ts` is more risk than we're willing to take. We're able to set a custom provider using `ethers` to get things like `deploy` working. However, when using `@openzeppelin/upgrades` plugin to call `deployProxy`, they access the hardhat network config provider directly instead of using our configured `ethers` provider, so deployment fails. I'm sure other plugins operate in the same way.\r\n",
