    "body": "From @fvictorio [on Discord](https://discord.com/channels/750408878008827925/750408878008827928/953617835077300224),\r\n\r\n> Something we want to have is some way to create a Hardhat environment programmatically. Something like `const hre = createHardhatRuntimeEnvironment(config)`. If we had that, you could create the config in an async way and then initialize the `hre` and use that. Still not the best solution, but better than the other workaround, and it would be useful in many other scenarios\r\n\r\nThis seems like it would work great. Is this planned and/or is there a GitHub issue I could follow or help out on? Our only alternative to get this working in the short term is to fork either Hardhat or the `@openzeppelin/upgrades` plugin. I'd much prefer to have a mainline solution to the problem so we can avoid forking.",
